<br>
Do the following: get a bracer of the hidden (market value 1-2kpp, or you can pharm it yourself, or borrow one from a guildmate). Summon a pet as far away from lenny as you can. Use pet hold if you can, otherwise have your e-boots and pet back off hot-keyed. Immediately hit your pet with your bracer (instant, right click, targetable see invis) Then ask a junior shaman to stack a buffer of crap buffs on him. Then get an aego and focus of spirit for the pet (pay for the buffs with mod rods). Then burnout 4 and SoS. If really paranoid grab a rune and spellshield for him too (again, pay for the buffs with mod rods). When lenny is engaged, send in the pet. Hit target self twice to target the pet, use your bracer of the hidden to refresh your pets see invis; then hit target self again and hit yourself with it too (to protect yourself from the dispell in case the AoE announcer lags). then make a mod rod, or rush lenny between AoEs to cast a nuke (choose based on the needs of your raid); then reapply see invis to your pet and yourself. Repeat as necessary. If pet drops below 30 life, hit him with a transons.<br>
<br>
This technique works for all WToV dragons, WW mini-dragons, Naggy and Vox, and for Klandicar. It works to a lesser degree on mobs with multi-dispell.<br>
<br>
I'll make an educated guess pet was doing 25 dps from meele. so in a 200 second battle that would be 5k damage. Not too shabby on a 200khp mob. On gozz, since the pet's procs will work, you can reasonablly expect to do double that. I'm not sure if the procs work on lenny or kland. <p>Master Cydmab Promethean, Triune <BR>
Level 60 Arch-Mage, Morell Thule <BR>
